    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-07-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-07-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="21"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d21">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890h.927/8</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-07-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 27, 1923</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received August 15.]</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 3329</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>:</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>Relative to the Department’s Instruction No. 639 of April 28, 1923, I beg to
                    inform you that, when the attitude of the United States Government was recently
                    presented to the Foreign Office, as reported in my despatch No. 2928 of March 7,
                    1923, it was once more emphasized that no American archaeologist would have any
                    difficulty in coming to an arrangement with Professor Foucher to dig in any part
                    of the country desired. As previously reported, it appears that Professor
                    Foucher did not desire an exclusive concession from the Afghan Government, but
                    that the agreement was drawn up in that form.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Myron T. Herrick</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
